==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stoichiometrical
<hw>Stoi`chi*o*met"ric*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos>
<def>Of or pertaining to stoichiometry; employed in, or obtained by,
stoichiometry.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>of, pertaining to, using, or
consuming, reagents in the exact proportions required for a given
reaction; <as>as, a <ex>stoichiometric</ex> reaction, <it>i. e.</it>, a
reaction which goes to completion, rather than stopping partway at an
equilibrium point</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stoichiometry</ent>⟦br⟧
